\id JHN - - Nama Back Translation
\c 1
\s Word of life
\p
\v 1 In the beginning(root) the Word already existed; the Word was(2 people was)with God, and the Word was God. \v 2 From the very beginning the Word was(between 2 people) with God. \v 3 Through his(him) God made everything; nothing appreared in every being made without him. \v 4 The Word was the source (of) life, and this life brought light to people. \v 5 The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness cannot pass/overcome it.
\p
\v 6 God sent his word carrying people(messenger), a man name Jon, \v 7 who came, told to the people about the light, so that all will hear the talk and truly approve(believe) it. \v 8 He himself was not the light; he came told about the light. \v 9 This was very real light which the light comes into the world and shines (on)to all the people.
\p
\v 10 The Word was in the world, and though God made the world through his(him), but the world did not know him. \v 11 He came to his own land, but his own peole did not accepted him. \v 12 But some people had accepted him and truly approved(believed) in him; he gave them the authority to become God's children. \v 13 They did not become God's children by physical birth nor by human's will or being born through physical father; but birth which is from God.
\p
\v 14 The Word became a man and lived among us, full of grace and truth. We saw his strong light(big light), which he received as the Father's only one Son.
\p
\v 15 Jon spoke about him. He shouted, "This is the one I was talking about when I said, 'He comes after me, but he surpasses me, because he first existed I was born later(existed before I was born).'"
\p
\v 16 By his full grace he has blessed us all, and gave us one blessing after other again. \v 17 God gave the law through Moses, but grace and truth came through him Yesu Keriso. \v 18 No one has seen God. The only one Son, who is God himself and who is close to the Father, whom put him clear.
\s Talk about Jon the baptisting man(baptist)
\p
\v 19 The Ju head men(head men) in Jerusalem sent some sacrifice offering man(burning sacrifice men) and people from Lefi group(Levites) to Jon to ask [him], "Who are you.s?"
\p
\v 20 Jon did not refuse to answer, but spoke openly and clearly, "I am not the Keriso."
\p
\v 21 They asked, "So who are you? Are you Elaija{m{
\f...f* {m{1.21 
Elaija 
explain who were waiting for by Ju

?"
\p
Jon answered them, "No, I am not him."
\p
They asked, "Are you the Prophet(man to making knowing God's knowledge)?
\p
He answered, "No."
\p
\v 22 They said, "Tell us who you are? We will take an answer to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?"
\p
\v 23 Jon answered in the talk of the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya:
\q1 "I am the voice of someone shouting in the clear place(desert){n{
\f...f* {n{1.23 
picture for printout

:
\q2 Make a straight way [for] the Lord to walk!"
\p
\v 24 The Farasi men who had been sent, \v 25 asked Jon again, "If you are not Keriso or Elaija or the Prophet, why do you do washing with water(baptize)?
\p
\v 26 Jon answered, "I put into(baptize) with water, but among you stands one who you do not know. \v 27 He is coming after me, but I am not enough to untie his sandol's rope."
\p
\v 28 All this happend there in Betani there the east side of the Joden River, where Jon was baptizing.
\s God's Lamb
\p
\v 29 The next day Jon saw Yesu coming to him, and said, "Look, here is God's Lamb, who takes away the sin of the world! \v 30 This is he who I was talking about and I said, "A man who is coming after me, he surpasses me, because he first existed I was born after." \v 31 I did not know about him, but I came batizing with water in order that it might put him clear to Israil people."
\p
\v 32 And Jon said this talk: "I saw the God Spirit(God Spirit) come down like as mamu/Note:looks like dove white bird/ from heaven and stay on him. \v 33 I did not know still that he was the one, but God, who sent me to baptize with water, had said to me, 'You will see the God Spirit come down [and] stay on a man; he is [the one] who will baptize with the God Spirit.' \v 34 Jon said, "I have seen this things and I tell you that he is the Son of God."
\s The first Disciples of Yesu
\p
\v 35 The next day Jon was standing there again with two in/of his following men, \v 36 when he saw Yesu walking, he said, "Look That's the Lamb of God"
\p
\v 37 The two following men heard(dual) him say this and went with Yesu. \v 38 Yesu turned, saw them(2 of them) following him, and asked (to 2 of them), "What are you(dual) looking for?"
\p
They.d answered, "Where are you staying, Rabai? (This name's meaning is "Teaching man(Teacher.")
\p
\v 39 He answered, "Come and to see." (It was 4 o'clock in the afternoon.) So they.d went with him and saw where he was staying and spent that day with him.
\p
\v 40 There is one of them was Endru, Saimon Fitè's younger brother, who heard what Jon had said and who had followed Yesu. \v 41 At once he went and saw his big brother Saimon and told him, "We have found Mesaya."(His name's meaning is "Keriso.") \v 42 Then he took Saimon to Yesu. Yesu looked at him and said, "Your name is Saimon son of Jon, but will be called Sifas." (This can translate Fitè and its meaning is "a rock.")
\s Yesu called Filif and Nataniel
\p
\v 43 The next day Yesu thought to go to Galili region. He found Filif and said to him, "Follow me!" \v 44 (Filif was from Betsaida, the town Endru and Fitè lived.) \v 45 Filif found Nataniel and told him, "We have found the one whom Moses wrote in the book of the law and who the God's people who make know(prophets) also wrote. He is Yesu the Josef's son from Najaret."
\p
\v 46 Nataniel asked, "Can anything good come from Najaret?"
\p
Filif answered, "Come and see."
\p
\v 47 When Yesu saw Nataniel coming to him, Yesu said about him, "Here is a real Israil man; to him there is no deceit!"
\p
\v 48 Nataniel asked him, "How do you know me?"
\p
Yesu answered, "I saw you when you were in the shadow of the breadfruit tree before Filif called you."
\p
\v 49 Nataniel answered, "Teacher, you are the Son of God! You are the ruling man(king) of Israil!"
\p
\v 50 Yesu said, "Your truly approve(believe) is it because I told you that I saw you in the shadow of the fig tree? Later you will look very big things happen that will surpass what you have seen now!" \v 51 And he said to them, "I am telling you the truth: you will find heaven open and God's men carrying heavenly message(angels)(heaven talk carring men) will go up and come down through the Son of Man."
\c 2
\s The wedding in Kana
\p
\v 1 Two days later there was a wedding feast in Kana town in Galili region. Yesu's mother was there, \v 2 and they invited Yesu and his following men to the wedding feast. \v 3 When the alcohol finished, Yesu's mother said to him, "Their alcohol has already finished."
\p
\v 4 Yesu answered her, "Mother, why do you tell me this? My day has not come."
\p
\v 5 Yesu's mother told the workers, "Do if what he tells you."
\p
\v 6 There were rules of Ju people about ritual washing, and so there were 6 stone jars for water carring, each one can hold between 80 litè or 120 litè. \v 7 Yesu said to the workers, "Fill these jars with water." They filled them to the brim, \v 8 and he told them again, "Now draw some water out and take it to the man who is looking after feast." They took him the water, \v 9 which had turned into alcohol, and he tasted it. He did not know from where this alcohol had come (but workers who had drawn out the water knew); so he called the bridgegroom \v 10 and said to him, "Everyone brings out the best alcohol first. When people have had plenty to drink, then they give people cheaper alcohol. But you.s are different. You.s have kept the best alcohol until now.’
\p
\v 11 Yesu did this first surprising things in Kana in Galili region; there he revealed his strong light(big light), and his following men truly approved(believed) in him.
\p
\v 12 After this, Yesu and his mother, small brothers and following men went to Kafenam and stayed there not for a many days.
\s Yesu went to the worshipping house
\p
\v 13 It was very close day for the Passover festival, so Yesu went to Jerusalem. \v 14 There in the worship house (worshipping house) area he found people exchanging cow, sheep and doves and also the money exchanging men sitting at their tables. \v 15 So he made a whip from the ropes and drove the all the people from the worshipping house, with their cows and sheep; he scattered their coins and turned over their money changing tables, \v 16 and he said to them who sold doves, "Take them out of here! Stop changing my Father's house a open space(market)!" \v 17 His following men remembered like that the verse says, "My love to your house burns in me like a fire."
\p
\v 18 The Ju head men came back at him with a question, "What surprising thing can you do to show us that you have the power(authority) to do this?"
\p
\v 19 Yesu answered, "Destroy this worshipping house, and in three days I will raise it up again."
\p
\v 20 They asked him, "What are you going to build it again in three days? To build this worshipping house took 46 years!"
\p
\v 21 But when Yesu said the worshipping house he said his body. \v 22 So when he was raised from death, his following men remeberd that he had said this, and they truly approved(believed) the Buk(scripture) and what Yesu had said.
\s Yesu know people's heart
\p
\v 23 While Yesu was in Jerusalem during the Passover festival, many truly approved(believed) in him because they saw the surprising things he did. \v 24 But Yesu did not depend on himself to them, because he knew all people. \v 25 There was no need any talk in order to say about them, because he himself knew what was in their hearts.
\c 3
\s Yesu and Nikodimas
\p
\v 1 There was one Ju head man name Nikodimas, who was in a Farasi group. \v 2 One night he went to Yesu and said to him, "Teacher, we know that you are a teaching man who God sent. No one can perform the surprising things you are doing unless God were/Note:dual/ with you."
\p
\v 3 Yesu answered, "I am telling you the truth: no one can see the ruling of God(God's reigning) unless he is born again."
\p
\v 4 Nikodimas asked, "How can a grown man be born again? He cannot enter his mother's womb and be born a second time!"
\p
\v 5 Yesu answered him, "I am telling you the truth, no one can enter the ruling of God unless he is born by water and the God Spirit. \v 6 A man is born in body from parents, but is born in spirit by the God Spirit. \v 7 You should not be surprised because I tell you that you must all(of you) be born again. \v 8 The wind blows to where it wants; you.s hear its sound which it makes, but you.s don't know from which way it comes or where it is going again. It is like that to them every people who is born by the God Spirit.
\p
\v 9 Nikodimas asked, "How this is?"
\p
\v 10 Yesu answered him, "You.s are a big teaching man in Israil, and you.s don't know about this? \v 11 I am telling you the truth: we speak what we know and report what we have seen, but still none of you.p willing to accept our talk. \v 12 Your.s big mind(faith) is not to me when I tell you.s about things of this world; how will you.s truly approve(believe) me when I tell you about things of heaven? \v 13 And no one has gone upto heaven except the Son of Man, who came down from heaven."
\p
\v 14 Just as Moses lifted up the steel/metal snake with a post in a desert, in the same way they must lift the Son of Man up/Note: there is no passive form in Nama/. \v 15 As a result, every people who truly approve(believe) him may have eternal life/note: literally they may be with eternal life/. \v 16 Because God loved the world so much, so he gave his only one Son, so that every people who truly approves(believes) in him may not die but have eternal life. \v 17 For God did not send his Son into the world in order to be his judging man, but to be his saving man.
\p
\v 18 Those who truly approve(believe) the Son are not judged; but those who do not truly approve(believe) have in judgement, because they did not truly approve(believe) God's only one Son. \v 19 This is how the judgement works: the light has come into the world, but people like the darkness and not the light, because their deeds are evil. \v 20 Those who do evil hate the light and will not come to the light, because they do not want their sin to put clear. \v 21 But those who do what is true come to the light so that other people can see that they do what God wants.
\s Yesu and Jon
\p
\v 22 After this, Yesu and his dicsiples went to Judia area, there he stayed with them and washed them with water.(baptized them) \v 23 Jon like that(also) was baptizing in Aeron village not far from Salim village, because there were plenty of water in that place. People were going to him and he was baptizing them. \v 24 After this was, [they] put Jon into darkness house.
\p
\v 25 Some of Jon's following men began arguing with a Jew about the matter of ritual washing. \v 26 So they went to Jon and told him, "Teacher, you remember the man who was with you on the east side of the Joden river, he is the one you spoke about? So he is baptizing now, and every people is going to him!"
\p
\v 27 Jon answered, "No one can have anything unless God gives him. \v 28 You yourselves are my watching men how I said, 'I am not him Keriso, but God sent me ahead of him.' \v 29 The new marrying man(bridgegroom) has new marrying woman, but the new bridgegroom's friend, who waits for and listens to him, he is joyful when he hears the new bridgegroom's voice. That joy is mine, is full. \v 30 He must become big but I must become low."
\s He who comes from heaven
\p
\v 31 He who comes from above surpasses all things. He who is from the earth belongs the earth and speaks about land things, but he who comes from heaven he is above all. \v 32 He reports what he has seen and heard, but no one accept his talk. \v 33 But whoever accept his talk confirms by [this]that God is truthful. \v 34 He whom God has sent speaks God's talk, because God gives him the fullness of God Spirit. \v 35 His Father loves his Son and has put everything in his power. \v 36 Who truly approves(believes) in the Son he has eternal life; whoever denies the Son will not be with life, but will leave into God's anger.
\c 4
\s Yesu and the Samaritan woman
\p
\v 1 The Farasi men heard that Yesu made people following him and baptizing so many people and his people became many and was surpassing Jon's following men. \v 2 But, Yesu himself did not baptize anyone; only his following man [do] \v 3 When Yesu heard this talk, he left Judia and went back to Galili region; \v 4 his returning was through Samaria area.
\p
\v 5 There in Samaria he came to a town name Sikar, which was not far from the ground which Jeikof gave to his son Josef. \v 6 Jeikof's water hole(well) was there, then Yesu, tired out because of walking, sat down there by the well at close noon.
\p
7-8\~
His following men went to the town in order to bring food. Then a woman from Samaria one came to draw water, then Yesu said to her, "Give me water."
\p
\v 9 The woman answered him, "You are a Ju man, and I am a woman from Samaria-then how can you asked me for a water? (Because Ju people will not share cups and bowls with Samaria people in eating.)
\p
\v 10 Yesu answered her, "If you knew what is God gift and who is he that is asking you for water, you will(would) ask him, and he will(would) give you living water."
\p
\v 11 The woman said, "Bigman, you have no drawing tool, and the well is deep. Where you would you get that life living water? \v 12 Our ancestor Jeikof gave us this water hole(well), he and his children and his all farming animal group(livestocks) drank water here. You surpass father Jeikof?
\p
\v 13 Yesu answered her, "Everyone who drinks this water will still be seeking water, \v 14 but whoever.single drinks the water I give them will never feel thirsty. Yes, the water this I gave them will become a flowing water in them will flowing by living life water and will give them forever life."
\p
\v 15 The woman said to him, "Bigman, give me this water in order that I will never feel thirsty and I will not come here to draw water."
\p
\v 16 Yesu told her, "Go, bring your.husband and come back."
\p
\v 17 She answered, "My.husband is not."
\p
Yesu said to woman, "You really said truth that your.husband is not. \v 18 But truth is, 5 husbands had brought you, and a man now who is not real your.husband. You have told me the truth."
\p
\v 19 The woman said, "Bigman, I know that you are a God's man who make know(prophet). \v 20 Our ancestors on this mountain worshipped God, but you Ju people say that Jerusalem is that place where we should worship God."
\p
\v 21 Yesu said to her, "Woman, Believe me, the day comes here where you.p will not worship the Father not on this mountain or there in Jerusalem. \v 22 You.p the people from Samaria don't know whom you.p worship, but we Ju people know whom we worship, because salvation comes from Ju people. \v 23 But the day is coming here and the day already come, where real worship people will worship God by God Spirit and truth, because such like worshipping people the Father wants. \v 24 God is Spirit, his worshipping people will worship by God Spirit and by truth."
\p
\v 25 The woman said, "I know that Keriso will come. When he comes, he will tell everything to us."
\p
\v 26 Yesu answered, "I am he, who I am talking to you."
\p
\v 27 In this moment, Yesu's diciples came back, and they came surprise they found him talking with a woman. But no one asked him, "What do you want? or "Why are you talking with woman?"
\p
\v 28 Then the woman left her water jar, went back to the town and said to people, \v 29 "Come, see this man who told me everything which I have done. Could he be Keriso?" \v 30 So they came from the town and walked/went to Yesu.
\p
\v 31 In this time the following men said to Yesu, "Teacher, Eat some food!"
\p
\v 32 But he said to them, "There is my food to eat that which you don't know about."
\p
\v 33 So the following men asked among themselves, "Has already someone brought him food?"
\p
\v 34 Yesu said, "My food is it is willing to do his will who sent me and willing to finish this work which he gave me to do. \v 35 You.p often say, 'It's 4 more months until harvest.' I tell you.pl, open your eyes look at the garden places! They are ripe in order to harvest. \v 36 And the one who digs out the harvest fields he gets pay and gathers the food things(crops) like to gather people for eternal life, so in order that the one who plants and the one who reaps will be(2 people) in happiness together. \v 37 Because the talk that is true, 'Some man plants and some man digs again.' \v 38 I have sent you in order to reap this which you have not worked for; other people had worked hard, and you.pl found the blessing from their work."
\p
\v 39 Many people from Samaria in that town truly approved(believed) in Yesu because the woman's trustful talk, "He told me everything I have done." \v 40 Then when people from Samaria came to him, they begged him to stay with them, and Yesu stayed there two days. \v 41 Many more truly approved(believed) him because his talk.
\p
\v 42 They said to the woman, "We don't truly approve(believe) because of what you said, now we ourselves already heard him, and we know that this man is really the Savior of the world."
\s Yesu makes good(heals) an Government worker's son
\p
\v 43 After the two days Yesu left and went to Galili region. \v 44 Yesu himself had said, "Prophets are not respected in their own area." \v 45 When he arrived at Galili region, the people there welcomed him, because they had gone to the Passover festival to Jerusalem and had seen everything what he had done to the festival.
\p
\v 46 Then Yesu went back to Kana in Galili region, where he had turned the water into alcohol. A government worker was there whose son was sick in Kafenam. \v 47 When this man heard that Yesu had arrived at Galili region from Judia, he went to him and begged Yesu in order to come to there and make good(heal) his son, who are close to death.
\p
\v 48 Yesu said to him, "None of you will truly approve(believe) unless you may see happening thing(surprising things) and surprising things(surprising things)."
\p
\v 49 The government working man answered, "Bigman, come with me before my son dies."
\p
\v 50 Yesu answered him, "Go; your son will be life.(live)"
\p
This man truly approved(believed) Yesu's talk then went. \v 51 When he went through the way, his without.payment working man(servant) men met him with this news that your boy is still life. \v 52 He asked them in which time he became good, they answered to him, "The fever sickness left him yesterday afternoon one o'clock."
\p
\v 53 Then his father rememberd that in that exact time Yesu had told him, "Your son will be life." So he and his whole family truly approved(believed) Yesu.
\p
\v 54 This was the second surprising thing which Yesu did after coming from Judia to Galili region.
\c 5
\s The healing there in the small lake
\p
\v 1 After this, Yesu went to Jerusalem for one of the Ju people's festival. \v 2 Close to Sheep's Gate in Jerusalem there is a small lake, which it they called Betsesda in Ibru language, and [which] is surrounded by 5 covered without wall house. \v 3 Through the covered without wall house so many people were lying- the blind men, the lame men and the paralyzed men. \v 4 Aman carrying heavenly message of the Lord would come down some time and spin the waters. When this happened, all sick people started going into small lake. The first man who got into the small lake became good, which desease he had.{o{
\f...f* {o{5.4 
This talk is not Jon wrote, but some teaching people thought this way.

 \v 5 One man was there who had been sick for 38 years. \v 6 When Yesu saw him lying there and knew that he had been in suffering this sickness for a long time, he asked him, "Do you want to become well?"
\p
\v 7 The sick man answered, "Bigman, to me nobody in order to help to put me in the small lake when the water is spinned. While I am trying to start to get into, other man goes down ahead of me."
\p
\v 8 Then Yesu said to him, "Get up, pick up your mat and walk." \v 9 Immediately the man became well; he picked up his mat and went.
\p
On which day this things happened was a Safat, \v 10 so the Ju head men said to this man who had became good, "This is the Safat; this is in our law you must not carry your mat."
\p
\v 11 But he answered, "The man who made me well told me , 'Pick up your mat and go.'
\p
\v 12 So they asked him, "Who is this man who told you to pick up and to walk?"
\p
\v 13 The man who became well did not know who it was, because Yesu had went quickly into the people group(crowd) there was.
\p
\v 14 Later Yesu found him there in the worshipping house place and said to him, "See, you are already turn to good. Stop doing sin or any bad [things] happen to you any more." \v 15 The man went away and told the Ju head men that Yesu made him good.
\s The Son's power(authority)
\p
\v 16 So because Yesu did this things in Safat for this Ju head men were spoiling him. \v 17 Yesu said to them, "My Father is always working, and I too must work." \v 18 For this reason they made it very much to kill him, not only was he breaking the Safat law but he was calling that God his Father was and in this way he had made himself equal with God.
\p
\v 19 Yesu gave them this answering, "I tell you truly that the Son can do nothing by himself, he can do only this what he sees which Father does, because whatever the Father does the Son also does. \v 20 Because the Father loves the Son and shows him all what he does. And Father will show him many big works that he [Jesu] will do, which will surpass the work he has already done, and you will be amazed. \v 21 Just as the Father raises the dead and give them life, in the same way the Son gives life to those who he wants to. \v 22 Because the Father does not do judgement to anyone, but he had gave all judgement to the Son, \v 23 in order that all the people may respect the Son just as they respect the Father. Whoever does not respect the Son does not respect the Father, who sent him.
\p
\v 24 I tell you the truth, whoever hears my talk and truly approves(believes) him who sent me for them will be eternal life and will not be in judgement but have already passed over from death to life. \v 25 I tell you the truth, the time is coming here and the day has already come where(when) the dead men will hear the voice of the Son of God, and those who hear it, they will become with life. \v 26 Just as the Father has life in himself, in the same way he has made his Son to have life in himself. \v 27 And he has given the authority to him to judge because he is the Son of Man.
\p
\v 28 Do not be surprised at this, beause the day comes here where(when) all who are in their graves will hear his voice, \v 29 and come out from their grave: those who have done good they will rise for life, and those who have done evil they will rise and put to punishment. \v 30 I can't do anything on my own authority; I do judgement only this how God tells me, therefore my judgement is straight, because I don't do my will but his [will] who sent me.
\s Reporting the true talk(Testimony) about Yesu
\p
\v 31 If I am going to report about mine, people would think my talk was not true. \v 32 But there is someone who reports on my behalf, and I know that what he says about me is true.
\p
\v 33 You have sent messengers to Jon and he had spoke about the truth. \v 34 But I don't accept people's reporting; but I say this in order that you may receive save. \v 35 Jon was like a lamp burning and shining light, and you were willing without-long(for a while) to rejoice in his light.
\p
\v 36 But I proclaim about myself something that surpasses Jon's talk, because I had done what Father gave me to do, and this things whch I did reporting the true talk that the Father has sent me. \v 37 And Father, who sent me, also reports the true talk about me. You have never heard his voice or seen his face, \v 38 and there is no his talk in your hearts, because you do not truly approve(believe) the one who he sent. \v 39 You.p read carefully the Buk(scripture), because you think that in that you will find eternal life. This Buk(scripture) speak about me! \v 40 But you refuse to come to me in order to take eternal life.
\p
\v 41 I am not looking for human praise. \v 42 But I know about you.pl, I know that to you.pl [there] is no God's love your hearts. \v 43 I have come in my Father's name, and you do not accept me; but if someone comes in his name, you will accept him. \v 44 You.p like to praise each other. That causes you.p happy. But you.p do not do goodthings in order that one who alone is God will praise you.p. That is why you.p will not truly approve(believe) me.
\p
\v 45 But I will no tell the Father that you have done wrong. Don't think that I will do that. No, he was Moses who will do that. You have hope that Moses is the one who will help you. But he is the one who will show you your wrong. \v 46 If you truly approved(believed) Moses, you would truly approve(believe) me, because he wrote about me. \v 47 But if you do not truly approve(believe) what he wrote, how are you going to truly approve(believe) what I say?"
\c 6
\s Yesu fed 5,000 adult men in the crowd
\p
\v 1 After this Yesu acrossed to far shore of Galili Sea(which is the Tiberias Sea). \v 2 And a big crowd followed him, because they had seen his doing things(special workings(miracles)) he made when he made good who was sick. \v 3 Yesu went up on the mountain/hill and sat down with them his following men. \v 4 The Ju people's Passover festival was near.
\p
\v 5 Yesu looked around and saw a large crowd was coming to him, so he asked Filif, "Where are we possible to buy food in order to feed all this people?" \v 6 He said this in order to test Filif, but he knew what he would do.
\p
\v 7 Filif answered him, "For every people to eat a little, it looks it will be about 200 denarion, which are wages for 200 days to buy enough bread."
\p
\v 8 One of his following men, Endru, who is Saimon Fitè's small brother, said, \v 9 "Here is a boy with 5 bread and two small fish. But that will not enough for these many people.
\p
\v 10 Yesu said, "Speak the people to sit down." There this place was with a grass to sit, so all the people sat down, about 5,000 adult men in the crowd. \v 11 Yesu took the bread, gave thanks to God and distributed it to the people who were there. In the same way he distributed the fish, and they all ate to which they wanted.
\p
\v 12 When they all satisfied to eat, Yesu said to his following men, "Pick up and gather. Let nothing be wasted." \v 13 So they gathered them all and filled 12 baskets with the pieces which left over from the 5 bread which the people had eaten.
\p
\v 14 Seeing this special things doing(miracle) which Yesu had did, the people there said, "Surely this is the Prophet who will come into the world!" \v 15 Yesu knew that they intended to come in order that they make him king by their want; so he went off again to the mountain/hill by himself.
\s Yesu walks on the water
\p
\v 16 When evening came, his following men went to the lake, \v 17 there got into a bout, and went back across the lake toward Kafenam. Night came on, and Yesu still had not arrive to them. \v 18 Then a strong wind was blowing and the waters became rough. \v 19 When the following men had rowed 5 or 6 kilometers, they saw Yesu coming with a walk on the water; and they were afraid. \v 20 Yesu told them, "Don't be afraid; I am." \v 21 Then they were happy to let Yesu get into the bout, and immediately the bout reached the land where they were going.
\s The people seek Yesu
\p
\v 22 On the next day the crowd which had left there on the other side of the lake knew that only one bout was there. They knew that Yesu had not entered in it with his following men, but following men themselves had left not with him. \v 23 Then some bouts from Tiberias landed near the place where the people had eaten the bread after the Lord had given thanks. \v 24 When this crowd knew that Yesu and his following men were not there, they got into those bouts and went to Kafenam seeking Yesu.
\s The life bread Yesu
\p
\v 25 When they found Yesu there on the other side of the lake, they asked to him, "Teacher, when did you arrive here?"
\p
\v 26 Yesu answered them, "I am telling you the truth, you are looking for me, not because you saw the surprising things I did but because you ate the bread and you satisfied. \v 27 Don't work for foodwhich will become bad, but work for this food which lasts for eternal life, which the Son of Man will give to you. Because to him the Father God has prepared his true approval.
\p
\v 28 Then they asked Yesu, "What can we do in order that we do what is God's will for us to do?"
\p
\v 29 Yesu answered them, "What God wants for you to do is to truly approve(believe) him who he sent."
\p
\v 30 So they asked Yesu, "What surprising thing will you do so that we may see this and truly approve(believe) you? What will you do? \v 31 Our ancesters ate mana there in the desert, just as it is written: 'He gave them bread from the heaven to eat.'"
\p
\v 32 Yesu said to them, "I tell you the truth, What Moses gave you.p [was] not the bread from heaven, but my Father gives you.p the real bread from heaven. \v 33 For God's bread is he who comes down from heaven and gives life to the land/world."
\p
\v 34 They said, "Bigman, always give us this bread."
\p
\v 35 Then Yesu told them, "I am life bread. Those who come to me will never be hungry; those who truly approve(believe) me will never be thirsty. \v 36 But as I told you, you have seen me but you do not truly approve(believe). \v 37 Everyone whom the Father gives me will come to me, and whoever comes me I will never drive away. \v 38 For I have come down from heaven not to do my want but to do his want who sent me. \v 39 And this is his want who sent me, that I shall not lose any of all those he has gave me, but I will raise them up at the last day. \v 40 For my Father's will/want is that all the people who look to the Son and truly approve(believe) him will be with eternal life, and I will raise them up at the last day."
\p
\v 41 The Ju people began to grumble about Yesu because he said that, "I am the bread which came down form heaven." \v 42 They said, "This man is Yesu, Josef's son, whose father and mother we know. How does he now say, 'I came down from heaven?'"
\p
\v 43 Yesu answerd them, "Stop grumbling among yourselves. \v 44 No one can come to me unless the Father who sent me draws them to me; and I will raise them from death at the last day. \v 45 The one of the God's people who make know(prophets) had written, 'God will teach every people.' All the people who listen to the Father and learn from him come to me. \v 46 No one has seen the Father only he who is from God; only he has seen the Father. \v 47 I tell you the truth, he who truly approves(believes) is with eternal life. \v 48 I am the life bread. \v 49 Your ancesters ate the mana there in the desert, but they died. \v 50 But this bread is which comes down from heaven, which people may eat of it and not die. \v 51 I am the living life bread which came down from heaven. Who eat this bread will live forever. This bread is my body, which I will give for the world to live the life.
\p
\v 52 Then Ju people began to argue heavily among them, "How can this man give us his body to eat?"
\p
\v 53 Yesu said to them, "I tell you the truth, if you.p do not eat the Son of Man's body and drink his blood, you.p will not be with life in yourselves. \v 54 Whoever eats my body and blood will be with eternal life, and I will raise them from death at the last day. \v 55 For my body is the real food, my blood is the real water for drinking. \v 56 Those who eat my body and my blood they will be in me, and I in them. \v 57 Just as the living Father sent me and I live because of the Father, so who feeds on me he will live because of me. \v 58 This is the bread which came down from heaven. Your ancesters ate mana and died, but those who eats this bread will live forever." \v 59 Yesu said this while in teaching in the meeting house in Kapenam.
\s Many discipes left Yesu.
\p
\v 60 When they heard this, many of his following men said, "This is a hard teaching. Who can listen to this talk?"
\p
\v 61 Yesu knew that his following men were grubling about this and said to them, "What this thing make you to stop following me? \v 62 How will be if you see the Son of Man go up to [the place] where he was before? \v 63 The God Spirit gives life; body/human's power is without.meaning. The talks which I have spoken to you.p come from God Spirit and gave a life. \v 64 But some of you do not truly approve(believe)." Yesu knew from the beginning who do not truly approve(believe) and who would give teeth(betray) him. \v 65 And he said more, "This reason I told you.p that no one can come to me but unless the Father make it possible for them to do."
\p
\v 66 This reason many of his following men turned back and would not follow him.
\p
\v 67 So Yesu asked 12, "Do you also want to leave?"
\p
\v 68 Saimon Fitè answered him, "Lord, to whom woud we go? You are with the talks of eternal life. \v 69 We truly approve(believe) and know that you are the Without.dust Man from God."
\p
\v 70 Yesu answered them, "I have chosen you 12. But one here is like a Sáifèr(Stan)!" \v 71 He spoke of Judas, Saimon Iskariot's son. Even though he was one of the Twelve, later he will give teeth(betray) him.
\c 7
\s Yeus and his small brothers
\p
\v 1 After this, Yesu went around Galili region. He did not want to go Judia because the Ju head men wanted to kill him. \v 2 But when from it the Ju festival of Shelters was near, \v 3 Yesu's small brothers said to him that, "Leave this area and go to Judia, so that your following men there will see your working things. \v 4 People don't hide what they are doing if they want to be known about theirs. If you do this things, the world will know about you. \v 5 Even his brothers did not truly approve(believe) him.
\p
\v 6 Yesu told them, "My day is not come yet; but your.p days are always ready. \v 7 The world cannot see you with hate, but it sees me with hate, because I reports that its ways are bad/evil. \v 8 You should go to this festival. I am not going to this festival, because my day has not come yet for me." \v 9 Yesu talked this talk, and he kept on stay in Galili region.
\s Yesu taught them pubically in the worshipping house area
\p
\v 10 After this his small brothers had gone to the place of festival, Yesu also went, not publicly, but secretly. \v 11 At the place of festival there the Ju head men were looking for Yesu and asked, "Where is he?"
\p
\v 12 Among the groups/crowds there was whispering about Yesu.
\p
Some said, "He is a good man." other people said again, "No, he is a liar who deceives the people." \v 13 No one talk about him openly because they felt fear about their head men.
\p
\v 14 When the festival became middle, Yesu went to the worshipping house area and began teaching. \v 15 The Ju head men were surprised and said, "How does this man know so much when he has never been to law school?"
\p
\v 16 Yesu answered them, "[It] is not my teaching, but it comes from who sent me." \v 17 Who want to do what God wants will know that my teaching is from God or from my making. \v 18 Who speak of their thought take respect only for themselves, but he who seeks this respect who sent him he is a true man; there is no lying in him. \v 19 Moses gave the law to you. But none of you keeps the law. Why are you trying to kill me?"
\p
\v 20 People answered him, "Evil spirit is to you! Who is trying to kill you?"
\p
\v 21 Yesu said to them, "I did one surprising thing(miracle) and you were all surprised. \v 22 Because Moses ordered you.p to cut the skin(circumcise) your.p sons though actually this is not from Moses, but from your.p ancesters , you do a circumcision sons in Safan. \v 23 If you.p cut skin(circumcised) a boy on the Safat so that you shall not break Moses's law, why are you angry with me because I made a man's body good on the Safat? \v 24 Don't examine by appearances, but examine by correctly.
\s What he is Keriso(Is he Keriso)?
\p
\v 25 Some people from Jerusalem said, "Is this man who they are trying to kill?" \v 26 Look! He is speaking in public, and any talk head men don't speak to him! Perhapes they think that he is really the Keriso. \v 27 But when Keriso comes, no one will know from where he is. But we all know from where this man comes."
\p
\v 28 While Yesu was teaching in the worshipping house area, he spoke with a loud voice, "Do you really know who I am and from where I am? I have not come on my decision. But he who sent me is true. You do not know him, \v 29 but I know him, because I came from him and he sent me."
\p
\v 30 Then they tried to make to catch him, but no one laid a hand on him, because his day had not come yet. \v 31 But many people in the crowd truly approved(believed) in him. They said, ‘This man has done so many special workings(miracles). Surely he is the Keriso. Miracle he do surpasses other people's.
\s They sent watching men(guards) to catch Yesu
\p
\v 32 Farasi men heard the crowd whispering like that about Yesu, so they and the sacrifice burning head men(chief burning sacrifice men) sent some watching men(guards) in order to arrest him.
\p
\v 33 Yesu said, "I will be with you a only little time, and I will go back again to [him] who sent me. \v 34 You.p will seek me, but you.p can't find me, because you cannot go to where I will be."
\p
\v 35 The Ju head men asked among themselves, "Where is he about to go [that] we shall not find him? Will he go to the Greek cities there our people live, and will teach the Greek people? \v 36 He says that we will seek him but we can't find him, and [that] we can't go where he will be. What does he mean?
\s Life giving spring water
\p
\v 37 There the last and very high(important) day in the festival Yesu stood and said in a loud voice, "Whoever feels thirsty come to me, \v 38 and whoever truly approves(believes) in me he will drink water. As the Buk(scripture) says, 'Life giving spring water will flow to them from belivers' inside.'" \v 39 When Yesu said this talk, he was saying that whoever truly approved(believed) would receive the God Spirit. At that day he did not give God Spirit to them, because Yesu was not lift to strong light(big light).
\s Division among the people
\p
\v 40 Some people in the crowd heard him say this and said, "This man is really this Prophet!"
\p
\v 41 Others said, "He is Keriso!"
\p
But other people said, "Keriso will not come from Galili region! \v 42 The Buk(scripture) says that Keriso will be Deifid's descendant and will be born in Betliem there where Deifid lived." \v 43 There was a division in the thought in the crowd about Yesu. \v 44 Some people wanted to catch him, but no one laid a hand on him.
\s Ju head men without big mind(faith)
\p
\v 45 When the guards went back, the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and Farasi men asked them, "Why did you not bring him?"
\p
\v 46 The guards answered them, "Nobody has talked like that he said!"
\p
\v 47 Farasi men asked them, "He deceived you.p also? \v 48 None of the head men or of the Farasi men truly approved(believed) in him? \v 49 But this crowd does not know the Moses's law. They are under God's judgment!"
\p
\v 50 One of Farasi men there was he Nikodimas, this man who came saw Yesu before. He said there to the other people, \v 51 "Our law did not allow that put people in a punishment, before we hear talk. We wan't count other until we understand well what he did."
\p
\v 52 They answered him, "Nikodimas, you are also from Galili region! Examine the Buk(scripture)s [and] you will learn that God's man who make know(prophet) never come from Galili region." \v 53 All the people went home,{p{
\f...f* {p{7.53 
Some knowleding people thought that the talk in 7:53 to 8:11 was not written by Jon, but another man wrote it later.
\c 8
\p
\v 1 but Yesu went to the Olif Mountain. \v 2 Early next morning he went to the worshipping house area. Many people came to him and Yesu sat and began to teach. \v 3 The law teaching men(teaching men of the law) and the Farasi men brought a woman who was found with other man who is not his husband(committing adultary) [and] made her stand before people. \v 4 They said to him, "Teacher, this woman had adultary and they saw her. \v 5 Moses's law taught us that, that kind of woman [people] must killed her with stone. How do you say?" \v 6 They gave the asking talk(asked) to trap Yesu. But Yesu bent down and began to write with hand on the ground. \v 7 When they were still asking him, Yesu stood up and said to them, "Who are you.s without doing sin throw a stone her first." \v 8 Again he bent and on the ground he began to write.
\p
\v 9 When they heard this talk, they all left, one by one, people big(adult) first to young people, until only Yesu left with woman still standing there. \v 10 Yesu stood up and said to her, "Woman, where are they? Who is left to condemn you?"
\p
\v 11 Woman answered him, "There is nobody, bigman."
\p
Yesu said to him, "I will not also condemn you. Go, but do not sin again."
\s Yesu the light of the world
\p
\v 12 When again Yesu spoke to the people, he said that, "I am the light of the world. Who follows me will not walk in the darkness and to him will have the light for giving life.
\p
\v 13 Farasi men said to him, "Now you had spoken about your own things. What you are saying has no authority."
\p
\v 14 Yesu answered them, "No, even though I said about myself, what I said is true, because I know from where I came and to where I am going. You have no-knowledge(don't know) from where I came and to where I am going. \v 15 You do judgement in a worldly way; I don't do judgment to anyone. \v 16 But if I do judgment, my decisions are true, beacuse I am not alone; the Father who sent me [is] with me. \v 17 There is written in your.p law that when two watching men(watching men) agree, what they say this is true. \v 18 I told about myself, and the Father who sent me he also report about me."
\p
\v 19 They asked him, "Where is your.s father?"
\p
Yesu answered them, "You don't know about me and about my Father. If you know about me, you would know about my Father also."
\p
\v 20 Yesu said all this talk when he taught there in the worshipping house area, there in the room where the offering box was placed. And no one held him, because his day not come yet.
\s You cannot go there where I am going
\p
\v 21 Again Yesu said to them, "I will go; you.p will seek me, but you.p will die in your.p sins. You cannot go there where I am going."
\p
\v 22 Then the Ju head men said, "He says we cannot go there where he is going. What this talk's meaning is, he will kill himself?"
\p
\v 23 Yesu answered them, "You.p are from this world here below, but I am from above. You.p are from this world, but I am not from this world. \v 24 That's why I already told you [that] you will die in your sins. And you will die in your sins if you do not truly approve(believe) that 'I Am Who I Am'."
\p
\v 25 They asked him, "Who are you?
\p
Yesu answered them, "What I told you.p from the base/beginning. \v 26 I have many judgement to you.p, which will put punishment. But who sent me he is true, and I tell to the world only that what I heard from him."
\p
\v 27 They did not know that Yesu spoke to them about his Father. \v 28 Then hHe said to them that, "When you lift up the Son of Man, you will know that 'I Am Who I Am'; then you will know that I don't do with my power(authority), but I say only that how talk the Father told to me. \v 29 Who sent me he is with me; he has not left me alone, because I always do his will."
\p
\v 30 Many people who heard Yesu say this reason they truly approved(believed) in him.
\s The truth will make you free
\p
\v 31 Yesu said to the people who is with big mind(faith) to him, "If you obey to my teaching talk, you will be true my following men; \v 32 you.p will know the truth, and the truth will make you free."
\p
\v 33 They answered to him, "We are Ebraam's descendant, and we have never been anyone's without.payment working men(servants). How can you say that, 'You will become free'?"
\p
\v 34 Yesu said to them, "I am truly telling you: every people who does sins he is without.payment working man(servant) of sin. \v 35 A without.payment working man(servant) has no permanent place in the family, but a son belongs to the family forever. \v 36 Then if the Son make you.s free, you.s will become really free forever. \v 37 I know that you are Ebraam's descendants. But you are making to kill me, because my talk are not in your heart. \v 38 I speak of what my Father showed me, but you do what your.p father has shown you."
\p
\v 39 They aswered him, "Our father is Ebraam!"
\p
Yesu answered to them, "If you are real Ebraam's children, you will do this work Ebraam did. \v 40 What all I did [is] I tell you the truth what I heard from God, but you are making to kill me. What Ebraam did not do such a thing! \v 41 But you.p do what your.p father does.
\p
They answered, "Only God is our Father, and we are his true children."
\p
\v 42 Yesu said to them, "If God is your.p Father, you.p will love me, because I came from God and now I am here. I did not come on my decision, but he sent me. \v 43 Why do you not carry/understand well my talk what I say? [It is] because you cannot carry/understand my talk. \v 44 You are your father's children, who is Sáifèr(Satan), and you want to follow your father's thinking. From the beginning/note: this word use for creation/he was a murderer, he was not true because his inside is no truth. When he tells with a lie, he is showing who is he, because he is liar and the father of lies. \v 45 But I tell the truth, and you don't truly approve(believe) me! \v 46 Who one [of you] can report my sin? Nobody. If I tell the truth, why do you not truly approve(believe) me? \v 47 Who belong to God they will listen God's talk. But you who do not belong to God, that's why you do not listen."
\s Yesu and Ebraam
\p
\v 48 They asked Yesu, " We are straight what we say that you are a Samaria man and to you a evil spirit came into!"
\p
\v 49 Yesu said, "In me there is no evil spirit. I respect my Father, but your.p respect is not to me. \v 50 I am not seeking big light(glory) myself, but God is going to big light(glory) me. He is the true judge. \v 51 I am telling you the truth: who obeys my talk he will never die."
\p
\v 52 They said to him, "Now we know truly you are with evil spirit! Ebraam already died, and the God's people who make know(prophets) also already died, but you say who obeys your teaching he will not die. \v 53 You surpass our father Ebraam, who already died? The God's people who make know(prophets) died already. How do you think who you are?"
\p
\v 54 Yesu answered them, "If I turn respect myself, that respect is without.meaning. But who respects me is my Father, this real meaning is [the one]who you say is your God. \v 55 You don't know him, but I know him. If I had said that I do not know him, I would be a liar like that you are. But I do know him and I obey his word. \v 56 Your father Ebraam was in joy because he would see the day of my coming; he saw it and was in joy.”
\p
\v 57 They said to him, “You are not even 50 years old, and you have ever seen Ebraam?”
\p
\v 58 Yesu answered them, “I tell you the truth, before Ebraam was born, I am who I am.”
\p
\v 59 Then they picked up stones to throw at him, but Yesu hid himself and left the worshipping house area.
\c 9
\s Yesu heals a man who was born blind
\p
\v 1 When Yesu he went, he saw him man blind from birth. \v 2 His following men asked Yesu, "Teacher, whose sin led to blind as he was born? His sin led or of his parent sins?"
\p
\v 3 Yesu said, "Not his sins or of his parent sins, but this happened in order that God's work will be shown through him. \v 4 While it is still day, we must do his work who sent me. Night comes, where no one can work. \v 5 While I am in the world, I am the world's light.
\p
\v 6 After he said this, he spit on the ground, made some mud with spittle, and he put it on the man's eyes. \v 7 He say, "Go, wash in Siloam the very wide water hole(well)"(This name's meaning is, "he sent him." Then this man went and washed, and came back to the house with eyes opened and was seeing.
\p
\v 8 His close friends/neighbors and [those] who had always seen him in begging asked, "This is a man who sat and begged. Is it true? \v 9 Some said, "Surely he is."
\p
Others said, "No, he is not; he just looks like him."
\p
But he himself said, "I am that man."
\p
\v 10 They asked him, "How were your eyes opened?"
\p
\v 11 He answered them, "That man name Yesu, he made mud and put it on my eyes and told me to walk to Siloam to forget. I went, and as soon as I washed, I start seeing."
\p
\v 12 They asked him, "Where is this man?"
\p
He said, "I don't know."
\s Farasi men ask about what happened to the blind man
\p
\v 13 They brought to the Farasi men this [man] who had been blind. \v 14 This day was Safat which Yesu mad the mud and opened the man's eyes. \v 15 Then Farasi men also asked him how he had saw. He told them, "He put mud on my eyes; I washed and now I see."
\p
\v 16 Some Farasi men said. "This man cannot come from God, because he does not respect/keep Sabbath's law."
\p
But other people asked, "How can sinner do like this surprising thing?" Then they began to divide of thought .
\p
\v 17 Then Farasi men asked the man again, "What do you say anything about him because he opened your eyes?"
\p
This man answered them, "He is a God's man who make know(prophet)."
\p
\v 18 But this Ju people people will not stoll truly approve(believe) that he was blind and had received for seeing, until they called his parents \v 19 and asked them, "Is this your.d son? Is this the one you.d say was born blind? How can he see now?"
\p
\v 20 His parents answered.dual them, "We.dual know that he is our son, and we know that he was born blind. \v 21 But we don't know how he is now able to see, and we don't know who cured him of his blind. Ask himself; he is big enough, and he will say for himself!" \v 22 His parents said.dual this because they.dual were afraid of Ju head people, who already made that [anyone] who say that Yesu was Keriso will be expelled from meeting house(meeting house). \v 23 That's why parents say like, "He is big, ask himself!"
\p
\v 24 So the head men again spoke to the man who had been blind. They said to him, ‘In front of God, without.lying talk(promise) that you will speak only true things. We know that this man is a sinner.’
\p
\v 25 He answered them, "I don't know he is sinner or not. One thing I know: I was blind but now I see!"
\p
\v 26 Then they asked him, "What did he do to you? How did he open your eyes?"
\p
\v 27 He answered, "I had told you before and you did not listen. Why do you want to hear again? Do you also want to become his following men?"
\p
\v 28 Then they insulted at him, and said, "You are that this man's following man! We are Moses' following men! \v 29 We know God spoke to Moses, but about this man, we don't know from where he comes!"
\p
\v 30 This man answered them, "That is surprising! You do not know from where he comes, but he opened me my eyes. \v 31 We know that God does not listen to sinners. He listens to [people] who respect him and do his will. \v 32 Nobody has ever heard of that eyes was opened of a man who had been born blind. \v 33 If this man were not from God, he couldn't what he did."
\p
\v 34 They answered him, "You were born and grew up in evil. You cannot teach us anything!" Then they drive him out.
\s Spiritual blindness
\p
\v 35 Yesu heard that they had cast him out, and when he found this man, Yesu said to him, "Do you truly approve(believe) the Son of Man?"
\p
\v 36 This man answered him, "Who is he, bigman? Tell me so that I can truly approve(believe) him."
\p
\v 37 Yesu answered him, "You have seen him, and he is the one who is talking with you now."
\p
\v 38 Then this man answered him, "Lord, I truly approve(believe) now," and knelt down before Yesu.
\p
\v 39 Yesu said, "I came to this world to judge, so that the blind men will/may see and those who see will/may become blind."
\p
\v 40 Some Farasi men who were with them hear him say this and asked, "Are we blind too?"
\p
\v 41 Yesu answered them, "If you were blind, you.p would not put punishment about sin, but you.p still say that you still see, your punishment still is."
\c 10
\s The parable of the watching man
\p
\v 1 Yesu said, "I tell you the truth: [anyone] who does not enter the gate of the sheep fence, but climbs in other way, he is a thief and a robber. \v 2 The man who eneters by the gate he is the watching man of the sheep. \v 3 The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, then the sheep listen to his voice when he call his own sheep by name, and he will lead them out. \v 4 When he brought all of his own out, he goes first, [and] his sheep next follow him, because they know his voice. \v 5 They will not follow other man, but they will run away from that man, because they do not know his voice.
\p
\v 6 Yesu told them this parable, but they did not carry/understand what he said.
\s Yesu the good watching man
\p
\v 7 Then Yesu said again, "I tell you the truth, "I am the gate of the sheep. \v 8 All other people who came before me they are the thieves and robbers, but the sheep did not listen to them. \v 9 I am the gate. Whoever enters through me will be saved; they will come in and go out to find the place with good grass. \v 10 The thief comes only for stealing, and killing and destroying. I come to give life and for full of life themselves.
\p
\v 11 I am the good watching man, who will die for the sheep. \v 12 The hired man, who is not a watching man and is not owner to sheep, whe he sees wild dog, he leaves the sheep and run away; wild dog destroys/attacks the sheep and [the sheep] scattered. \v 13 The hired man runs away because he works for payment and does not think about the sheep. \v 14 I am the good watching man; I know my own sheep and they know me, \v 15 as Father knows me and I know the Father, and I am willing to die for them. \v 16 There are other sheep which belong to me which are not in this sheep fence. I must bring them, they will listen to my voice, and they will become one group(flock) with one watching man. \v 17 The Father loves me because I am will to die, so that I may take it back again. \v 18 No one takes my life from me. I choose to die. I have power/authority to take it away and I have authority to bring it back. This is what my Father has commanded I should do.
\p
\v 19 Again there was a division of thought among Ju people because of these talks. \v 20 Many people said like that again, "He is with a evil spirit(evil spirit possessed)! He is a crazy! Why you.pl listen to him?"
\p
\v 21 But other people said, "You.p must know the man with a evil spirit could not talk like this! How could a evil spirit can make blind people good?"
\s They rejeted Yesu
\p
\v 22 It was at winter[this Nama word means the time when there are heavy rain and it is hard for people to travel] the remembering festival the our ancesters gave the worshipping house to God was in Jerusalem. \v 23 Yesu was walking around Solomon's setset(it's like a veranda where people sit and walk around, without wall)in the worshipping house area, \v 24 when the Ju people gathered round and asked him, "How long will you delay reporting us? Tell us the truth: are you Keriso?" \v 25 Yesu answered, "I already told you, but you.p do not truly approve(believe) me. This works which I do in my Father's name shows you.p who I am. \v 26 but you do not truly approve(believe) me because you are not my sheep. \v 27 My sheep listen to my voice; I know them, and they follow me. \v 28 I give them eternal life, and they shall never die. No one can take them away from my hand. \v 29 My Father has given them to me. He surpasses everything, no one can take them away from my Father's hand. \v 30 the Father and I are one."
\p
\v 31 The Ju people again picked up stones to throw Yesu. \v 32 Yesu said to them, "I did many good things in your presence which the Father gave me to do; for which work are you.p going to stone me?"
\p
\v 33 They answered, "[It is] not we are going to stone because of all of good things/deeds, but because of your without respecting talk(blasphemy)! You are only a body(man), but you yourself claim to be God!"
\p
\v 34 Yesu answered them, "It is written in your own law [that] God said, 'You are small gods.' \v 35 We know that what the Buk(scripture) says this is true and forever; and God called these people small gods, these people to whom he gave his talk. \v 36 As for me, the Father chose me as his own and sent me into this world. Why you said that I have a blasphemy(said a without respecting talk), because I said that I am God's Son? \v 37 Do not truly approve(believe) me unless I am doing my Father's work. \v 38 But if I do them, even though you do not truly approve(believe) me, truly approve(believe) my deed, in order that you may know truly that the Father [is] in me, and I in the Father."
\p
\v 39 Again they tried to seize Yesu, but Yesu escaped from their hands.
\p
\v 40 And Yesu crossed the Joden again river to where Jon baptized, and there he stayed. \v 41 Many people came to him and said to each other, "Jon never did a special workings(miracles), but everything he had said about this man is true." \v 42 Many people there truly approved(believed) in him.
\c 11
\s The Death of Lajarus
\p
\v 1 A man name Lajarus was sick. He was from Betani, their village of Meri and her big sister Mata. \v 2 This Meri, whose brother Lajarus laid sick, she herself was the same who later poured good smell's liquid(perfume) on the Lord's feet and wiped them with her hair. \v 3 So the sisters.dual sent talk to Yesu, "Lord, the one whom you love is sick."
\p
\v 4 When he heard this, Yesu said, "This sickness will not to be death. No, it is for God's big light(glory) so that God's Son will be lifted through this. \v 5 Yesu loved Mata and her little sister and Lajarus. \v 6 But when he heard that Lajarus was sick, he still stayed that place for two more days. \v 7 Then he said to his following men, "Let us go back to Judia."
\p
\v 8 They said, "Teacher, on short time ago there the Ju people tried to stone you and again to [there] you are going back?"
\p
\v 9 Yesu answered them, "There are 12 hours of one daytime. Person who walks in the daytime he will not fall down, because he can see it by this world's light. \v 10 If he walks at night he will fall down, because he has no light." \v 11 After he said, he told them, "Our friend Lajarus is sleeping; but I am going to there to wake him up."
\p
\v 12 His following men answered him, "Lord, if he is sleeping, he will become good." \v 13 Yesu spoke of his death, but his following men thought an idea about bodily(natural) sleep he might speak.
\p
\v 14 That's why he told them again straightly, "Lajarus has died, \v 15 and for your.pl reason(sake) I am in happiness I was not there, in order that you may truly approve(believe). But let us go to him."
\p
\v 16 Then Tomas who is called Didimas he said to the other discipes, "We will go, we may die with him Yesu."
\s Yesu is the ressurection and the life
\p
\v 17 On his arrival Yesu found [that] Lajarus has already been buried and has become 4 days. \v 18 Betani was only three kilomitè from Jerusalem, \v 19 many Ju people came to them Mata and Meri, help them because their brother Lajarus has died. \v 20 When Mata heard [that] Yesu was coming, she went and met him, but Meri stayed in house.
\p
\v 21 Mata said to Yesu, "Lord, if you were here my brother would not have died. \v 22 But I know that now God will give you what you ask."
\p
\v 23 Yesu said to him/her, "Your brother will rise again." \v 24 Mata answered him, "I know he will rise again on the last day." \v 25 Yesu said to him/her, "I am the rising and the life. For him who truly approves(believes) in me will be alive even though he potentially died, \v 26 and whoever lives and truly approves(believes) in me he will not die. Do you truly approve(believe) this?"
\p
\v 27 Mata answered him, "Yes, Lord, I truly approve(believe) you that you are Keriso, God's Son, who has come to this world.
\p
\v 28 After this when she said this, he went back and called her small sister Meri outside and said, "Teacher is here and he is calling you."
\p
\v 29 When Meri heard, she quickly stood up and went to him. \v 30 Yesu has not arrived yet to the village, but there still was this on the place where Mata met him. \v 31 When Ju people who were with Meri in the house, supporting her, they saw how fast she stood up and went out, they followed her, thinking that to the grave she might go to cry.
\p
\v 32 When Meri arrived this place where Yesu was and found him, she fell to his feet and said, "Lord, if you were here, my brother would not die."
\p
\v 33 When Yesu saw her weeping, and Ju people who came with her they also in the same way weeping, he felt deep sadness in the heart. \v 34 He asked them, "Where have you make land(buried him)?"
\p
They answered him, "Come and see, Lord."
\p
\v 35 Yesu started crying. \v 36 Then Ju people said, "See how much he loved him!"
\p
\v 37 But other people were saying, "He made the blind become good. Why he not protect Lajarus from dying?"
\s Yesu raised Lajarus from the dead
\p
\v 38 Yesu felt deep sadness in the heart, came to the grave. It was a hole and stone covered on the door. \v 39 He said, "Take this stone away." Mata dead person's sister said, "Lord, now bad smell will be, because he has been 4 days."
\p
\v 40 But Yesu said, "What I told you [that] you will see God's strong light(big light) if you truly approve(believe)."
\p
\v 41 This is why they took the stone away. Then Yesu looked up and said, "Father, I give thanks you have heard me. \v 42 I know that you always hear me, but I am saying this for the people are standing here, so that they may truly approve(believe) that you sent me."
\p
\v 43 When he said this, Yesu shouted with a loud voice, "Lajarus, come out!" \v 44 Dead person came out, his hands and feet were wrapped with grave clothes and with clothes tied around the head.
\p
Yesu said to them, "Untie grave clothes and let him walk."
\s The secret thought made(plan) to kill Yesu
\p
\v 45 For this many Ju people who had came to visit Meri, and had seen what Yesu did, truly approved(believed) in him. \v 46 But some people went to Farasi men and told them what Yesu did. \v 47 Then the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and Farasi men called a Ju head men' gathering(meeting).
\p
They asked, "What shall we do? This man is making many special workings(miracles). \v 48 If we continue let him to do this things, all the people will truly approve(believe) him, and then Rom people will come destroy our worshipping house and our place(nation)
\p
\v 49 A man name Kayafas, who was leading burning sacrifice men in that year, said to them, "You don't know about it! \v 50 You don't know that it is good for one man to die for the people, by that all Ju people will not be destroyed."
\p
\v 51 He did not say this by his will, but because he was leading burning sacrifice men in that year, he said this talk for the future that Yesu will die for Ju people, \v 52 and not only for Ju people, but also for those scattered God's children to bring back and make them one. \v 53 So from that day they planned to kill Yesu.
\p
\v 54 Because of this Yesu didn't openly walk among Ju people. But he retreated and went to town name Efaraim, which close to the desert, where they stayed with his following men.
\p
\v 55 It was almost time for the Ju Passover festival to begin. Many people were going from their long(country) places to Jerusalem. They were going there to make themselves clean in front of God before they went to the festival. \v 56 They kept looking for Yesu, and when they was standing in the worshipping house place, they started asking among themselves, "How are you thinking? What he will come in this feast really(true)?" \v 57 But the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and Farasi men gave announcement that whoever saw Yesu where he was, he must tell us in order that they would arrest.
\c 12
\s Yesu anointed at Betani
\p
\v 1 6 days before to the Passover fastival Yesu arrived in Betani, where Lajarus was staying whom Yesu raised from the death. \v 2 Food there they prepared for Yesu(Note: we can translate, Food was prepared there for Yesu), Mata was serving the food and Lajaris was one of them who was sitted at the food table. \v 3 Meri took with a big money bottle of good smell liquid from soem flowering tree named nad and poured it on Yesu's feet and wiping his feet with her hair. Then the sweet smell filled the house.
\p
\v 4 One of his following men, Judas Iskario, who will make teeth(betray) him later, said, \v 5 "Why don't this good smell liquid(perfume) sell for 300 Denarion, which are the wages for 300 days and the money given to the poor?" \v 6 He said this, he really did not take care of the poor but because he was a thief. He carried the money bag and helped himself from it.
\p
\v 7 Yesu answered him, "Leave her alone! She keep this special smelling liquid for the day of my making land(burial). \v 8 You always will be with the poor, but I will not always be with you."
\p
\v 9 Many Ju people had heard that Yesu was in Betani, so they went there, because to see Yesu and to see Lajarus like that, whom Yesu raised from death. \v 10 The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) made plan to kill Lajarus like that, \v 11 beacuse of his reason many Ju people were rejecting Ju head men and they were only believing in Yesu.
\s Yesu entered into Jerusalem like the ruling man(king)
\p
\v 12 The next day the large crowd who had come for Passover festival heard that Yesu was coming to Jerusalem. \v 13 They took palm leaves, and went out to meet him, shouting, "Praise to God! Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord! Blessed is the ruling man(king) of Israil!"
\p
\v 14 Yesu found a young donkey and sat on there, as the Buk(scripture)s were written,
\q1 \v 15 "Don't be afraid, big place(city) of Jaion{q{
\f...f* {q{12.15 
Jaion 
This is Jerusalem

!
\q2 See, your.p the ruling man(king) is coming,
\q2 is sitting on the young donkey."
\p
\v 16 Yesu's following men did not understand all this at that time. They understood only after Yesu was with big light(glory). Then they remembered that someone had written these things about him in the Bible.
\p
\v 17 The people who were with Yesu when he called Lajarus from the grave and raised him from death were reporting/testifying what had happened. \v 18 Many people because they had heard Yesu had did this surprising thing, went out and go to meet him. \v 19 Farasi men said among themselves, "You.p see we can do nothing, all the people in this world are following Yesu!"
\s Yesu told about his death
\p
\v 20 Some Grik people were there among those who went to worship at the feast. \v 21 They came to Filif, who was from Betsaida in Galili region, they said to him, "Bigman, we want to see Yesu." \v 22 Filif went and told Endru, Endru and Filif came.dual, told.dual Yesu.
\p
\v 23 Yesu reply to them, "The days has come for the son of Man to be lifted up \v 24 I tell you the truth, unless the seed of flour fall into the ground and dies, it is still one seed, but if it dies, it will produce many seeds. \v 25 The man who loves his life will lose it, when which man hates his life in this world will keep it for eternal life. \v 26 Anyone who wants to be my without.payment working man(servant) must follow me. Then he will be with me, where I am. My Father will praise anyone who is my without.payment working man(servant).
\p
\v 27 Now my heart is in trouble, and what will I say? Father, save me from this day. No, for this reason I came for this day. \v 28 Father, lift up(glorified) your name!"
\p
Then a voice came from heaven, "I have lifted it up(glorified), and will lift it up(glorified) again." \v 29 The crowd that was there, heard and said that it was a thunder; other people said a man carrying heavenly message must have spoken to him.
\p
\v 30 Yesu said, "This voice was for your.p reason, not my reason. \v 31 Now is the time for judging to the world; now the ruler of this world will be thrown away/note: original word order-[they] will throw away the ruling man(king) of the world outside/ \v 32 When they lifted me up from this earth, I will cause all people to come to me." \v 33 He said this in order to show in which way he was to die.
\p
\v 34 The crowd said, "We had heard from the Scripture that Keriso will live forever. Why do you say they will lift the Son of Man up? Who is this Son of Man?"
\p
\v 35 Then Yesu told them, "To you.p will be the light for a short time. Walk while the light is to you.p, so that the darkness does not surpass you. The man who walks in the darkness doesn't know where he is going. \v 36 Put your.p mind to the light while it is to you, so that you will become sons of the light." When he finished talking, Yesu left them and hid himself from them.
\s The Ju people still did not truly approve(believe)
\p
\v 37 Even though Yesu did all these special workings(miracles) in their presence, but they did not truly approve(believe) him. \v 38 This happened as what God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya has said:
\q1 Lord, who truly approved(believed) our talk?
\q2 And to whom still did the Lord show his power?"
\p
\v 39 For this reason they did not truly approve(believe) him because Aisaya had also said:
\q1 \v 40 "The Lord made their eyes blinded
\q2 and hardened their heart again like that,
\q1 in order that they will not see with their eyes,
\q2 will not know in their hearts,
\q2 will not turn and I would make them good."
\m
\v 41 Aisaya said this because he saw Yesu's strong light(big light) and spoke of him.
\p
\v 42 But many head men truly approved(believed) in Yesu. But because of Farasi men they did not report about their big mind(faith) for fear because they take them out from the meeting house(meeting house), \v 43 because they took praise from men so much not from God.
\p
\v 44 Yesu said with an loud voices, "When a man truly approves(believes) in me, he does not truly approve(believe) only me, but he also truly approve(believe) who sent me. \v 45 When he looks at me, he sees him who sent me. \v 46 I have came [as]a light to this world, so that whoever truly approves(believes) in me he will not be in the darkness.
\p
\v 47 Which man hears my talk and does not obey them, I do not report him court/judgement. Because I did not come to judge the world, but to save them. \v 48 There is a judge for the one who rejects me and does not truly approve(believe) my talk; this talk which I have spoken will condemn them on the last day. \v 49 I don't say my own talk, but the Father who sent me told me to speak what I have spoken. \v 50 I know that his commanding talk leads us to eternal life. So what I only speak like as how Father told me to say.
\c 13
\s Yesu washed his follower(following man)'s feet
\p
\v 1 The passover feast was close. Yesu knew that the day has come for him to leave this world and to go back to his Father. He loved his followers in this world, he loved them very much to the end.
\p
\v 2 In the afternoon meal, Sáifèr before caused Judas, Saimon Iskariot's son, who made a plan to give teeth(betray) Yesu. \v 3 Yesu knew that his Father gave all things under his power, and he came from God and was about to go to God. \v 4 Then he stood up from the meal, took off his outside clothing, and tied himself on the waist with a towel. \v 5 After this, he poured the water in the dish, and started washing his followers' feet, then wiped dried them with this towel which was tied him.
\p
\v 6 He came to Saimon Fitè, who told him, "Lord, do you wash my feet? I don't want."
\p
\v 7 Yesu answered him, "Now you do not know what I am doing, but later you will know"
\p
\v 8 Fitè said, "Never, you will not wash my feet not now or forever."
\p
Yesu answered him, "If I do not wash your feet, you will not be my follower."
\p
\v 9 Saimon Fitè answered him, "Then, Lord, not only my feet but my hands and my head like that."
\p
\v 10 Yesu answered him, "Those who had been washed only their feet need to be washed; their whole body is without dirt(clean). You are clean but not all of you." \v 11 Hhe said that because he knew who would give teeth(betray) him, and for this reason he said all people were clean but not one.
\p
\v 12 When he finished washing their feet, he wore his clothes and returned sat in his place. Yesu asked them, "Have you known what I have done to you? \v 13 You call me, 'Teacher' and 'Lord' and you say straight, I am really this. \v 14 Just like me, your.p Lord and Teacher, I have washed your.p feet in the same way you.p must wash one another's feet. \v 15 I did the surprising thing in order that you.p can do them in the same way what I did for you.p. \v 16 I tell you the truth, a without.payment working man(servant) will not surpass his owner, and messenger will not surpass him who sent him. \v 17 Now you know about these thing, you will be in blessing(blessed) when you do them.
\s Yesu told about his betrayal
\p
\v 18 I am not talk about all of you.p, I know whom I have chosen. But in order to become true this Scripture, 'He who eats my food, he is my man who give teeth(betrayer).'
\p
\v 19 I am telling you.p now before it happens, in order that when it happens, you will truly approve(believe) me that I am who I am. \v 20 I tell you the truth: whoever receives a man who I send receives me; and whoever receives me receives him who sent me."
\p
\v 21 After when Yesu said this talk, he was trubled in sprit and said to his followers, "I tell you the truth, one of your man will give teeth(betray) me."
\p
\v 22 His following men started looking at each other, because they did not know whom Yesu spoke. \v 23 One of his follower whom Yesu loved was close to Yesu. \v 24 Saimon Fitè motioned with hands and said to this follower, "Ask him which man do he speak?"
\p
\v 25 Then this following man leaned to Yesu, he told Yesu, "Lord, who is this man?"
\p
\v 26 Yesu answered him, "He will be this to whom I will give bread piece when I will dip it in the dish. Then he dipped the bread piece [and] gave it to Judas, Saimon Iskariot's son. \v 27 As soon as Judas took the bread, Sáifèr entered him. Yesu told him, "What you begin to do, do it fast." \v 28 But in the feast no one know why Yesu told it to him. \v 29 Because Judas hold their money bag, one thought that Yesu might tell him to buy things for the feast, or to give some things to the poor. \v 30 As soon as Judas received the bread, he went out. And it was night.
\s Yesu told him Fitè's denial
\p
\v 31 As soon as he went, Yesu said, "Now people will see how big the Son of Man is. In this reason they will see how big God is. \v 32 If God is glorifiedIbig light) in him,God will glorify the Son in himself, and will glorify him at once.
\p
\v 33 My children, I will be here with you for a while. You.p will seek me, and I tell you what I told the Ju people: Where I am going, you cannot go there.
\p
\v 34 The new law/command I give you, love other people, just as I love you, therefore you love each other. \v 35 In this all people will know that you are my followers, if you love each other.
\p
\v 36 Saimon Fitè asked him, "Lord, where are you going?"
\p
Yesu answered him, "Where I am going, you cannot follow me today, but later you will follow."
\p
\v 37 Fitè asked him, "Lord, why I cannot follow you now? I'm ready to die for you."
\p
\v 38 But Yesu answered him, "You really will die for me? With true I tell you, firstly you will deny me three times, later the chicken will shout!"
\c 14
\s Yesu comforted his followers
\p
\v 1 Don't let your.p heart be trouble. Believe God and also truly approve(believe) me. \v 2 My Father's house has many rooms; if it was not true, I would not report that I am going there to prepare a place for you.p. \v 3 If I go to prepare your place, I will come back and take you to myself so that you will be there where I am. \v 4 You know the way to this place where I am going."
\s Yesu is the way to the Father
\p
\v 5 Thomas said to him, "Lord, we don't know where you are going, how can we know the way?"
\p
\v 6 Yesu answered him, "I am the way and the truth and the life. Without me no one can go to the Father, only through me. \v 7 If you have known me, you will know in the same way my Father. From now you know him and have seen him."
\p
\v 8 Filif said, "Lord, show us the Father and only this we want."
\p
\v 9 Yesu answered him, "You should know me, Filif, I was with you for a long time. Which man has seen me have seen the Father. Why are you saying, 'Show us the Father'? \v 10 Don't you truly approve(believe) that I am in the Father, and the Father is in me? The talk I am saying to you.p are not my own. But this is the Father is staying in me, who is doing his work. \v 11 Believe me when I am saying that I am in the Father and the Father is in me. If not, truly approve(believe) me because of things I have done. \v 12 I tell you the truth, which man truly approves(believes) in me will do this things what I have done. The action he will do will surpass very big things that I continally do, because I am going to the Father. \v 13 And I will do whatever you.p ask in my name, so that Father's strong light(big light) will show through the Son. \v 14 You.p ask to me whatever you may in my name, and I will do it.
\s Talk without lying(promise) about God Spirit
\p
\v 15 If you.p love me, you will obey to my commands. \v 16 And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another Helper. That Helper will stay with you.p forever. \v 17 He is theGod Spirit of the truth. The world cannot receive him, because it cannot look at him or cannot know him. But you know him because he stays with you and will be in you.p. \v 18 I will not leave you like orphan children, I will still come to you.p. \v 19 In a little while, the world will not see me, but you.p will see me. Because I live, you.p will also live. \v 20 On that day you.p will know that I am in my Father, and you are in me and I am in you.p. \v 21 Those who have my laws and follow them, they are the one who love me, my Father will love every people who love me, and I will love them and show myself to them."
\p
\v 22 Judas(not Judas Iskariot) said, "Lord, why will you show yourself only to us but not to the world?"
\p
\v 23 Yesu answered him, "If whoever loves me, he will follow my teaching. My Father will love him, and we will come to him and stay with him forever. \v 24 He who does not love me will not follow my teachings. These talk you.p hear are not my own, they are his my Father's who sent me. \v 25 I have spoken these things to you while I am still with you. \v 26 But Helper, The Spirit of God(God Spirit), whom the Father will send in my name, will teach all things. He will help you.p to remember all what I have said to you. \v 27 Peace I leave with you; my peace I give to you; not as the world gives do I give to you. Do not allow your.p own hearts trouble and don't be afraid.
\p
\v 28 You.p have heard I said, I will go and will come back to you again. If you.p love me, you will be happy in my going to the Father; because the Father surpasses me. \v 29 I have told you later it will happen, in order that when it happens you.p may truly approve(believe). \v 30 I will not speak that long, because this world's head man is coming. But he is without power over me, \v 31 but the world must know that I love my Father and I do exactly how my Father told me.
\p
"Come, let us leave this place.
\c 15
\s Vine and branches
\p
\v 1 I am the true vine, and my Father is a farmer. \v 2 He cuts every branches in me which does not produce fruit, and he prunes which one produce fruit, so that they will be very fruitful. \v 3 You are pruned because of the talk which I have spoken to you. \v 4 Remain in me, and I will still be in you.p. No other brance will just produce fruit by itself unless it joins to the vine. In the same way you.p yourselves cannot produce fruit unless you.p are still in me.
\p
\v 5 I am the vine, and you are branches. If a man still is in me and I am in him, he will produce many fruits; without me you cannot do anything. \v 6 If you still are not in me, you are like branches that they throw them away and it becomes dry. People pick them up, throw them to the fire and burn. \v 7 If you are still in me, and my talk still in you, ask whatever you.p want, and [God] will do it to you.p. \v 8 This is my Father's big light(glory) by that you produce many fruits, and you show yourselves are my followers.
\p
\v 9 Just like Father loved me, and I loved you.p, you must continually stay in my love. \v 10 If you obey my talk, you will still be in my love, just like I had obeyed Father's talk and I am still in his love. \v 11 I have told you this in order that my joy will be with you.p and in order that your.p joy may be full.
\p
\v 12 This is my commandment; love each other just like I have loved you.p. \v 13 Very high love to your friends is to give your life for them. \v 14 You.p are my friends if you.p do what I said. \v 15 I do not call you without.payment working men(servants) without pay, because the without.payment working men(servants) will not know about his owner's work, but I call you friends, because everything what I have known from the Father I have made you.p known. \v 16 You.p did not choose me, but I chose you and appointed you in order that you will go to produce fruit, fruit which will exist. And for what you.p may ask in my name, the Father will give it to you.p. \v 17 This is my commandment: love one another.
\s The world hates Yesu's followers
\p
\v 18 If the world hates you.p, you.p must remember that They had hated me first. \v 19 If you were of the world, it will love you because you are its own. But you are not of the world, and I have chosen you from the world. In this reason world hates you. \v 20 Remember the talk I had told you: 'The without.payment working man(servant) does not surpass his master. If they persecuted me, they will also persecute you in the same way. If they hear to my teaching, they will also hear to your teaching. \v 21 They will persecute you in what way because of my name because they do not know who sent me. \v 22 If I would not come and talk to them, they would not have been guilty of sin; But now they cannot say, we did not do wrong. \v 23 Who hates me also hates my Father in the same way. \v 24 If I had not done special workings(miracles) to them which no one did, they would not been guilty of sin. But in what way they have seen and they still hated me and my Father. \v 25 But this is to fulfill what they wrote in their law, 'They hated me without reason.'
\p
\v 26 When the Helper comes, whom I will send to you.p from the Father, God Spirit of truth who will come form the Father, he will report(testify) about me. \v 27 You.p also in the same way must report about me, because you.p have been with me from the beginning.
\c 16
\p
\v 1 I have told all this you in order that you.p will not stop from the big mind(faith). \v 2 They will take you.p out of the gathering house(meeting houses), the day is coming here when those who beat you.p to death will think by this way he is doing the work for God. \v 3 They will do these things because they do not know the Father or me. \v 4 I have told you this, in order that when this day arrives to them to do this things, you.p should remember what I told you.
\s The work of the God Spirit
\p
"I did not tell you in the beginning because I was with you \v 5 But now I am going to him who sent me, but no one asked me, 'Where are you going?' \v 6 And now I have told you.p about this, big sadness has filled your.p hearts. \v 7 But I tell you the truth, this is for your good that I am going. Because if I do not go, the Helper still will not come to you.p, but if I go, I will send him to you.p. \v 8 When he comes, he will show the people of this world what they are like. He will show that they are wrong. They do not know what sin really is, they do not know about who is straight with God and they do not know God's judgement. \v 9 They do not know correctly what sin is, because they do not truly approve(believe) me; \v 10 They don't know about straightness, because I am going to the Father and you.p will not see me again. \v 11 And they do not know about judgement, because now head man of this world is standing in judgement.
\p
\v 12 I have many things to say to you.p, but now there are too much for you to truly approve(believe). \v 13 But when he, the God Spirit of truth comes, he will teach you in all the truth. He will not talk on his own. He will only say what he hears, and he will tell you what will happen later. \v 14 He will bring strong light(big light) to me, because he will take what I am saying and will tell it to you.p. \v 15 All what is of the Father are mine. That is why I say that God Spirit will take what is mine and tell it to you.p.
\s Sadness will turn to joy
\p
\v 16 In a little while you will not see me; again a little while, and you will see me again. \v 17 Some of his following men said themselves, "What does he mean by saying that, 'just for a little while you.p won't see me again and not long(a little while) after you.p will see me again,' and 'because I go to the Father'? \v 18 They were still asking, "What does he mean that just for a while? We can't carry what he is saying!"
\p
\v 19 Yesu already knew that they wanted to ask him about it, because of this he said to them, "Why are you asking among yourselves what I mean when I said that, 'just for a little while, you will not see me and for a liitle while later you will see me again'? \v 20 I tell you.p the truth, you.p will cry and be sad but the world he is still be joy. You.p will be sad but later your.p sadness will turn to joy. \v 21 When woman is giving birth there is pain because her day has come, but when a woman gives birth a child, she forgets the pain because of her joy that the child has arrived to this world. \v 22 So with you: Now is your sad day, but I will see you.p again and you.p will rejoice, and no one takes your joy. \v 23 On that day you.p will not ask me for anything. I tell you the truth: my Father will give you.p whatever you.p ask in my name. \v 24 Until now you.p have not asked for anything in my name; ask and you.p will take and your joy will be full.
\p
\v 25 I have spoken eampletalk, in order to explain to you.p what I had spoken, the day is coming here where I will not speak this example talk but I tell you clearly about my Father. \v 26 On that day you will ask in my name, I did not say that I will ask the Father for you.p. \v 27 No, the father himself loves you because you.p have loved me and had truly approved(believed) me that I came from God. \v 28 I came from the Father and arrived to the world, now I am leaving the world and going back to the Father."
\p
\v 29 Then Yesu's followers said, "Now you.s are speaking clearly to us and are not speaking example talk we did not understand it. \v 30 Now we have seen that you.s know everything, and you.s don't need anyone who give you.s asking talk. Because of this, we truly approve(believe) you truly have come from God.”
\p
\v 31 Yesu answered them, "Do you.p truly approve(believe) me now? \v 32 But the day is coming here, and it is here, where you.p will scatter to your own home, you will leave me alone, but I am not alone, I am with my Father. \v 33 I have told you.p about this in order that in me to you will be peaceful way. In this world to you will be heavy/hard thing, but be courageous! I have overcome the world.
\c 17
\s Yesu talked with God(talked with God) about himself
\p
\v 1 After Yesu said this, he looked up to the sky/heaven and said:
\p
"Father, the time has come. Give big light(glory) to your Son in order that the Son will give you the big light(glory). \v 2 You gave him power/authority for all people, in order that he will give them eternal life to all those whom you gave him. \v 3 Eternal life's meaning is that they know you, the only true God, and know Yesu Keris, who you sent. \v 4 I have brought you big light(glory) to the world by finishing the work what you have given me to do. \v 5 Father, give me the big light(glory) in your present now, give me the same shape big light(glory) [that] you gave me [and] I had with you before the world was made.
\s Yesu talked to God(talked with God) about the followers
\p
\v 6 I have shown you.s to those who you.s have given me from this world. They were yours; you.s gave them to me. They have obeyed your.s talk. \v 7 Now they know that everything you gave me came from you. \v 8 I gave them this talk you gave me, and they received. They know that this is true I came from you, and they truly approved(believed) me that you sent me. \v 9 I talk with God to You God for them. I am talking with God to You not for this world, but for those whom you.s have given me, because they are yours. \v 10 All what is mine are yours, and all what is yours are mine; and my big light(glory) shines through them. \v 11 I will not stay in this world that long, but they will still stay in this world, and I am about to go back to you. Without.dust Father, talk care of them with your power name, which name you gave me, in order that they will be one just as we are one. \v 12 When I was with them, I took care of them with your power name, which you gave me. I took care of them and none was lost only one but who was marked, in order that Buk(scripture) might become true.
\p
\v 13 I am about to go back to you.s now, but I am saying about this things while I am still here in this world in order that all my joy will be with them. \v 14 I gave them your talk, but the world saw them with hate(hated them), because they are not of this world just as I am not of this world. \v 15 My talking with God is not in order that you take them out of this world, but in order that you will take care of them from the evil man. \v 16 They are not of this world, I am same not of this world. \v 17 Make them clean with your true talk; your talk is true. \v 18 As you have sent me to this world, I am also sending them to this world. \v 19 For them I give myself to you, so that they will also be truly given to you.
\s Yeu talked to God(talked with God) about all truly approves(believes)
\p
\v 20 My talking with God is not only for them. I also talk with God for those who will truly approve(believe) me through their preaching talk, \v 21 in order that they all will be one, Father, just as you are in me and I am in you. They may also be in us in order that the world will truly approve(believe) that you have sent me. \v 22 I gave them this big light(glory) which you gave me, in order that they will be one, just as we are one. \v 23 I in them and you in me, in order that they will really become one, in order that will let the world know that you sent me and loved them in the same way as you loved me.
\p
\v 24 Father! I want those whom you gave me will be with me there where I am, and they will see my big light(glory), this big light(glory) which you have given me because you loved me, before the world was made.
\p
\v 25 Righteous Father! The world do not know you, only I know you, and the approving truth people know that you sent me. \v 26 I made your name know to them, and I will still contine to make it known, in order that your love for me will be in them, and I myself will be also in them."
\c 18
\s [They] held Yesu(Yesu held)
\p
\v 1 When he finished talking with God, Yesu went with his followers going across Kidron creek. In the other side was a olif treegarden, he and his followers went there.
\p
\v 2 Judas, who gave teeth(betrayed) him, knew this place because Yesu used to meet in this place with his followers. \v 3 Then Judas came to the garden with soldiers and some worshipping house guards [who] chief burning sacrifice men and Farasi men sent. They were carrying lamps, bark torches and weapons.
\p
\v 4 Yesu, knowing all what was going to happen to him, went up and asked them, "Who are you.p looking for?"
\p
\v 5 They answered him, "Yesu of Najaret."
\p
Yesu said, "I Am."
\p
Judas, the man who give teeth(betrayer) was standing there with them. \v 6 When Yesu said, "(That) I Am," they moved back and fell down to the ground.
\p
\v 7 Again Yesu asked them, "Who are you looking for?"
\p
They said, "Yesu of Najaret." \v 8 Yesu answered them, "I have told you that I am he. If you are looking for me, let my followers go." \v 9 Yesu said this because earlier he had said about this, "I have lost none of those people that you gave to me." This made what he had spoken earlier really happen.
\p
\v 10 Saimon Fitè had a sword. He took hold of it and he attacked the without.payment working man(servant) of the leading burning sacrifice man. He cut off the without.payment working man(servant)'s right ear. This without.payment working man(servant)'s name was Malkus. \v 11 Yesu told Fitè, "Put back your sword to it's sheath. I should drink this cup of pain which the Father has given me."
\s They took Yesu to Anas
\p
\v 12 Then the soldiers and their head man and worshipping house guards they caught Yesu. They bound him. \v 13 And they brought him first to Anas. Kayafas was married to daughter of Anas. Kayafas was leading burning sacrifice men that year. \v 14 Kayafas was the one who told Ju people that it will be good if one man dies for all people.
\s Fitè first denial
\p
\v 15 Saimon Fitè and another follower followed.dual Yesu. This leading burning sacrifice men knew this Yesu's following man, so he went with Yesu into leading burning sacrifice men's house yard, \v 16 but Fitè still waited outside at the door, but the other Yesu's following man who the leading burning sacrifice man knew, he came back, told the girl who was the door keeper, and brought Fitè in.
\p
\v 17 The girl who was at the door she asked Fitè, "You are one of his following men, true you are?"
\p
But Fitè answered him, "I am not."
\p
\v 18 It was cold, workers and the worshipping house guards stood on the side of the fire which they tried to keep warm. Fitè himself stood warming by the charcoal fire.
\s The leading burning sacrifice men asked Yesu
\p
\v 19 Next, the leading burning sacrifice man asked Yesu about his following men and about his teaching.
\p
\v 20 Yesu answered him, "I have spoken openly this world, I always taught in the gathering houses(meeting houses) and in the worshipping house area, where all the Ju people gathered one place, I did not speak anything secretly. \v 21 Why do you ask me? Ask those heard me, they know what I said."
\p
\v 22 When he said this, one of the worshipping house guard who stood close to him hit him on the face and said, "You should not speak to the leading burning sacrifice man in that way."
\p
\v 23 Yesu answered him, "If I have said wrongly, just say where is the wrong. But if I have said truly, why did you hit me?"
\p
\v 24 Then Anas sent Yesu bound to Kayafas the leading burning sacrifice man.
\s Fitè's denied again
\p
\v 25 While Saimon Fitè was standing warming by the fire, they asked him, "You must also be one of his follower."
\p
He denied and said, "I am not."
\p
\v 26 One of leading burning sacrifice men's without.payment working men(servants), the family of whose ear Fitè cut off, he asked him, "What I did not see.dual you with him there in the garden?" \v 27 Again Fitè denied, at these time the rooster cried out.
\s Yesu before Failet
\p
\v 28 So Ju people led him from the house of Kayafas to a Rom governor's house. It was early in the morning, but they still did not go into the house, because they would become unclean, they would not allow them for passover meal to eat. \v 29 Then Failet came out to them and asked, "What wrong thing do you say that this man has done?"
\p
\v 30 They answered him, "If he was not a wrong doer, we would not hand him over to you."
\p
\v 31 Failet said, "Take him yourselves and ask him by your law. "
\p
The Ju people answered him, "But we have no straight to put someone to death." \v 32 This fulfilled what Yesu spoke how he will die.
\p
\v 33 Failet went back into the house, called Yesu to himself and asked him, "Are you the ruling man(king) of the Ju people?"
\p
\v 34 Yesu asked him, "What this asking talk came from you, or did other people report about me?"
\p
\v 35 Failet answered him, "I am not a Ju man. Your own people and your chief burning sacrifice men they handed you to me. What did you do?"
\p
\v 36 Yesu said, "My reigning place is not of this world. If it was, my without.payment working men(servants) would fight and prevent me from Ju people arrest. But now my reigning place is of another place."
\p
\v 37 Failet said, "So, you are the ruling man(king), really?"
\p
Yesu answered him, "You are straight as you say that I am the ruling man(king). Rightly, for this reason I was born came to this world to report about the truth. All those are from the truth listen to me."
\p
\v 38 Failet asked him, "what is truth?"
\p
After Failet had said this, he again went out to the Ju people and said, "I did not find anything bad from which he will pay. \v 39 But this is your own custom for me in order that I will take out to you.p one darkness house man(prisoner) this Ju people's Passover day. Do you want I am going to take out the ruling man(king) of the Ju people?
\p
\v 40 They answered him loudly, "Not him, but Barabas!" Barabas was a thief.
\c 19
\s They sent Yesu to be hung on the cross
\p
\v 1 Failet sent soliders to whip Yesu. \v 2 The soldiers took some branches with thorns and they made a crown for Yesu. They put it on his head. Then they took a purple coat and they put that on him. They did all this as if he was the ruling man(king). \v 3 and came up to him, repeatedly saying, "Ei(making fun of him), the ruling man(king) of the Ju people!" And they continue to hit him on the face.
\p
\v 4 Once more Failet went out and said to the Ju people, "Look, I am bringing him again to you.p in order to let you know that I did not find anything bad from which he will get a payment/charge." \v 5 When Yesu came out wearing the crown of thorn on the head and wearing purple cloth, Failet said to them, "Here is the man!"
\p
\v 6 When the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the worshipping house guards saw Yesu, they shouted, "Nail on the cross! Nail on the cross!" But Failet answered them, "You take him and hang him. As for me, I didn't find any badness which he should get a payment/charge."
\p
\v 7 The Ju people replied, "To us here is a law, and in this law he should die, because he claimed that he was God's Son."
\p
\v 8 When Failet heard this, he filled afraid very much, \v 9 and he went back into the house. He asked Yesu, "Where are you from?" But Yesu gave no answer. \v 10 Failet said to him, "You do not want to talk to me? Remember that I have authority. I can let you go free, or I can let them kill you on a cross.
\p
\v 11 Yesu answered him, "You would not have this power to overcome me unless he(God) gave them to you.s from heaven. Therefore he who handed me to you, his sin surpasses your sin."
\p
\v 12 Then form there Failet tried to make take Yesu out, but the Ju people still continually shouting, "If you let this man go, you will not be a friend of big the ruling man(king) Kaisar! Which people who claim that they are the ruling man(king) oppose Kaisar!"
\p
\v 13 When Failet heard this, he brought Yesu and sat down a seat for judging man This seat was a place called the Wide stone, Gabata in Ibru talk." \v 14 This day was a preparing day for the Passover feast; it was midday.
\p
Failet said to the Ju people, "Your.p the ruling man(king) is here!"
\p
\v 15 But they shouted, "Kill him! Kill him! Nail him on the cross!"
\p
Failet asked them, "What I will nail the ruling man(king) on the cross?"
\p
The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) answered him, "To us are no other ruling man(king) but only Kaisar!"
\p
\v 16 Finally Failet handed him over to them in order to be nail on the cross.
\s The nailing
\p
Then the soldiers took Yesu. \v 17 He was carrying his own cross, to this place called the Skull, (this is Ibru language which is called "Golgota." \v 18 There they nailed Yesu on the cross. They put two other men on crosses near to Yesu. They were on each side of him and Yesu was between them.
\p
\v 19 Failet also wrote a letters/notice and put it on the cross. He wrote like this; "Yesu of Najaret, the ruling man(king) of the Ju people." \v 20 Many Ju people read notice, because there on this place where they nailed Yesu on the cross was not far to the town, this notice was written in Ibru, Latin and Grik. \v 21 The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) of Ju people went to Failet and said, 'Do not write like, "The ruling man(king) of the Ju people." But, write, "This man said that he is the ruling man(king) of the Ju people."
\p
\v 22 Failet answered him, "What I have written, I must have written."
\p
\v 23 And when the soldiers nailed Yesu to the cross, they removed the clothes and divided them into four groups and each soldier got one. They did that and then they got the long cloth worn inside and saw that cloth was not sewn from many pieces, but it was done from one piece from the top to the down.
\p
\v 24 They said among themselves, "We will not tear it, we will play dice game and see who will get it." This happened in order that it will become true which says, "They divided my garment among themselves and played dais game for my clothing." So like this the soldiers did.
\p
\v 25 Near the cross of Yesu stood his own mother, his mother's younger sister, and Meri who was a wife of Klofas, and Meri Makdalin. \v 26 When Yesu saw his mother there, his following man whom he loved was standing close to them, he said to his mother, "Woman, this is your son." \v 27 Then he said to that following man, "Here is your mother." From that time, that following man of Yesu looked after Yesu's mother in his house.
\s The Death of Yesu
\p
\v 28 After this, Yesu knew that he had finished the work. And in order to make the Scripture become true, Yesu said, "I am thirsty." \v 29 There laid a jar of sour alcohol; then they made a sponge there they soaked it and with a stick of Isof tree lifted it to Yesu lips. \v 30 When he drank this alcohol, Yesu said, "It is finished!"
\p
With that talk he bowed his head and died.
\p
\v 31 There was on the preparing day, and the next day was Safat. Because the Ju people did not want dead bodies to hang on the cross on the Safat, they asked Failet to break the legs to die quickly and to take down the bodies. \v 32 The soldiers went there. They broke the legs of the two men who were on the crosses next to Yesu. \v 33 But when they went to Yesu and found that he had died they did not break his legs. \v 34 But one of soldiers pierced side of Yesu with a spear, at once, blood and water poured out. \v 35 The man who saw this thing made to report/testfy, and his report/testimony is true. He knows that he reports the truth, and he reports in order that you will also truly approve(believe). \v 36 This thing happened in order that the Buk(scripture) would become true: "Not one of his bones shall be broken," \v 37 and another Buk(scripture) says, "They will look on him whom they pierced with the spear."
\s Making land for Yesu
\p
\v 38 Later, Josef from Aramatia town asked Failet for the body of Yesu. Josef was a following man of Yesu, but secretly because he fell with fear the Ju people. With only Failet's permission, he came and took the body of Yesu. \v 39 Nikodimas, who at first visited Yesu in the night, he himself brought about(like) 34 kilogram mixtured special smelling liquid from mirè and aloe. \v 40 These two men took and wrapped Yesu's body with cloth with special smelling liquid, they did these in the way of the Ju's burial. \v 41 At this place where they nailed Yesu on the cross, there was a garden, in this garden was a new hole in the rock, where no one was made land(buried). \v 42 Because it was Ju people's preparing day and the tomb was close, they laid Yesu.
\c 20
\s The rising
\p
\v 1 On early Sunday morning, when it was still dark, Meri Makdalin came to the tomb and saw the stone had been moved from the door. \v 2 Then she ran found Saimon Fitè and the other following men of Yesu, whom Yesu loved, and said, "They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have put him!"
\p
\v 3 So Fitè and the other following man went to the tomb. \v 4 Both of them were running, but the other following man of Yesu passed Fitè and arrived first at the tomb. \v 5 He bent over and looked into, the clothes lying there but he did not go in. \v 6 Then Saimon Fitè who was following after him arrived and went into the tomb saw the cloths lying there. \v 7 He saw the cloth which Yesu's head was wrapped. This cloth rolled up itself differently from other cloth. \v 8 Then this following man who arrived first to the tomb also went inside, he saw and truly approved(believed). \v 9 They.d did not know Buk(scripture) that Yesu will rise from the death. \v 10 Then Yesu's following men went back to their house.
\s Yesu appears to Meri Makdalin
\p
\v 11 But Meri still stood outside the tomb crying. When she was still crying, she bent over looked into the tomb \v 12 and saw two men carrying heavenly message(angels) dressed in white, they.dual were there where Yesu's body had been laid, the other sat the head and the other at the feet.
\p
\v 13 They.dual asked her, "Woman, why are you crying?"
\p
She said "Because they have taken my Lord away and I do not know where they had put him." \v 14 From there, she turned around and saw Yesu there, but still she did not know that it was Yesu.
\p
\v 15 He said, "Woman, why are you crying? Whom are you looking for?"
\p
She taught that it might be a farmer, she said, "Bigman, if you have taken him away, tell me where you have put him and I will bring him."
\p
\v 16 Yesu said to her, "Meri."
\p
She turned to Yesu and said in Ju people's language, "Raboni!"(it means teaching man)
\p
\v 17 Yesu said, "Do not hold me, because I am not still ascending to the Father. Go to my group(brothers) and tell them, 'I am beginning to ascend to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.'"
\p
\v 18 Meri Makdalin went and told Yesu's following men, "I have seen the Lord!" and she told what Yesu had said to her.
\s Yesu arrived/appeared to his following men
\p
\v 19 When it was evening on the same day on Sunday Yesu following men gathered only one place in the house and close the door in fear of the Ju people, Yesu came stood among them and said, "Peace be with you!" \v 20 After he said these, he showed his hands and his side to them. His following men started rejoicing when they saw the Lord.
\p
\v 21 Again Yesu said, "Peace be with you.p! As the Father has sent me, I am also sending you.p." \v 22 With that he breathed to them and said, "Receive the God Spirit. \v 23 If you wash anyone's sin, [his sins] will be washed; if you do not wash their sin, this is not washed."
\s Yesu appeared to Tomas
\p
\v 24 But Tomas(who they called Didimas), one of the 12 following men of Yesu, was not there when Yesu came to other following men. \v 25 So other following men of Yesu told him, "We have seen the Lord!"
\p
But he said to them, "Unless I see the nail marks on his hands and touch my finger where they nailed him, and touch my hand into his side where they pierced him with the spear, I will not truly approve(believe)."
\p
\v 26 A week later Yesu's following men were into the house again, and Tomas was there with them. They closed all the doors still Yesu went in stood in their mids and said, "Peace be with you!" \v 27 Then he said to Tomas, "Put your finger here, see my hands. Reach out your hand and put it into my side. Do not doubt [and] believing."
\p
\v 28 Tomas told Yesu, "My Lord and my God!"
\p
\v 29 Then Yesu told Tomas, "Because you have seen me, this is why you truly approve(believe) me, blessed are those who do not see me but by big mind(faith) they truly approve(believe) me."
\p
\v 30 Yesu did other many surprising things while his following men were with him, which I did not record them in this book. \v 31 But these writing are in order that you may truly approve(believe) that Yesu is Keriso, God's son, and if you truly approve(believe) him, you may have life in his name.
\c 21
\s Yesu appeared at the sea of Galili
\p
\v 1 After this Yesu appeared again to his following men, there by the sea of Galili, and it happened like this. \v 2 Saimon Fitè, Tomas(other name Didimus), Nataniel from Kana in Galili region area, two of the sons of Jebedi and the two other following men of Yesu who were all there. \v 3 Saimon Fitè told them, "I am going to catch fish."They said, "We'll go with you.s." So they went and got into the bout, but that night they catch nothing.
\p
\v 4 Early in the morning, Yesu stood on the shore, but his following men did not know that it was Yesu.
\p
\v 5 He called out to them, "Friends, do you any fish you catch?"
\p
They answered him, "No."
\p
\v 6 He said, "Throw your net on the straight side of the bout and you will catch some fish." When they did, they were unable to pull the net into the bout because they caught so many fish.
\p
\v 7 The following man whom Yesu loved said to Fitè, "This is the Lord!" As soon as Saimon Fitè heard him say, "It is the Lord," Saimon Fitè wrapped his outer garment which he took off for working tied it over his body jumped into the water, swam to shore. \v 8 But the other following men of Yesu followed with a bout they were dragging nets full of fish. And they were not far from the land, but about 100 mitè to the shore. \v 9 When they landed, they saw the charcoal fire with fish lying on it, and some bread.
\p
\v 10 Yesu said to them, "Bring some fish which you have caught." \v 11 Saimon Fitè got into the bout and started pulling the net to the shore. It was full of large fish, 153 of them but the net did not break. \v 12 Yesu told them, "Come and have food." But his following men were afraid to ask him, "Who are you?" They knew that it was the Lord. \v 13 Yesu came, held the bread and gave it to them, and also did with fish in the same way. \v 14 This was the third time Yesu appeared to his following men, after rising from the dead.
\s Yesu and Fitè
\p
\v 15 When they finished eating food, Yesu said to Saimon Fitè, "Saimon Jon's son, do your loving me surpass these other following men loving me?"
\p
He said, "Yes, Lord, you know that I love you."
\p
Yesu said, "Feed my lambs."
\p
\v 16 Again Yesu said, "Saimon Jon's son, do you truly love me?"
\p
He answered him, "Yes, Lord, you know that I love you."
\p
Yesu answered him, "Take care of my sheep."
\p
\v 17 The third time Yesu said to him, "Saimon Jon's son, do you truly love me?"
\p
Fitè felt pain because Yesu asked him third time, "Do you love me?"
\p
He said, "Lord you know everythings; you know I love you."
\p
Yesu said, "Feed my sheep. \v 18 I tell you the truth, when you were still young you had dressed youself and went where you wanted to go. But when you become old you will raise your hands, and other people will dress you and lead you where you do not want to go." \v 19 Yesu said this in order to show how Fitè would die and where Fite would glorify God by this death. Then he said to him, "Follow me!"
\p
\v 20 Fitè turned and show Yesu's following man whom Yesu loved following them. (This was he who leaned to Yesu there at the meal and had said, "Lord, who will give teeth(betray) you?) \v 21 When Fitè saw him, he asked, "Lord, how about him?"
\p
\v 22 Yesu answered him, "If I want him to be still alive until I return, how is this to you? You should follow me." \v 23 For that reason talk became wide among his friends that this Yesu's following man will not die. But Yesu did not say that he would not die, he only said, "If I want him to live untill I return, how is that to you?"
\p
\v 24 This Yesu's following man was who told about this and who wrote them. We know that his report is true.
\p
\v 25 Yesu did many things likewise, if everything they would have written, there would not be enough spaces in the earth to put the books.
